0. PREAMBLE

The GNU Affero General Public License is a free software license
you can use when you want to make sure that all modified versions
of your program and all software that uses it (through a network)
stay free.  It is a version of the GNU General Public License
(GPL) that includes an additional provision for software that is
run on servers.

When you use AGPL-licensed software, you get the freedom to run it,
to study and change it, and to redistribute copies of your original
or modified software (the last two freedoms are sometimes called
"free software").  You also have the added freedom of ensuring
that any modifications you make to the software are made available
to others so they can benefit from your changes.

This license applies to any program that incorporates the
software licensed under this license, and it allows you to make
full use of the software while ensuring that any future
modifications remain free.

